> username of 8 characters = 8 bytes
> if maximum of 256 characters not set, buffer overflow is possible
> Buffers are stored in data structures, called memory stack
> push adds element to stack
> pop removes last inserted element
> in modern stacks in arrays:
  > int A[3] = {2, 3, 4};       // bottom
  > int B[2] = {7, 9};          // topped up
> if attacker can write in B, an overflow to A is possible
  > int overflow[4] = {1, 1, 0, 0};
